      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm working on a paper for my linguistics class and i'm kind of stuck on how to talk about competence in writing. like, if you look at these two excerpts from a student's journal, which one comes across as more \"intelligent\" or \"academically competent\" in a formal university setting?\n\nText A: \"The data suggests a significant correlation between the two variables, indicating that the hypothesis may be partially supported under specific conditions.\"\n\nText B: \"The results showin that them two things definitely connected, so the idea they had is kinda working out for the most part.\"\n\nWhich one would a professor take more seriously in a research paper?",
