      "content": "i mean, i get that text A is more formal, but isn't there a difference between being \"uneducated\" and just using a different dialect? like, if the person who wrote text B is actually a genius but they just speak AAVE, does the \"lack of formal preparation\" you mentioned actually reflect their intelligence, or is it just a bias in how we judge certain ways of speaking? wouldn't a linguist say both can be equally \"competent\" in their own context?",
